<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-17T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-17T23:00:00-05:00" n="29" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/18691a:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)<note n="61" xml:id="d29fn61">Marginal note: “OK FDR.”</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-17T23:00:00-05:00">January 17, 1942—11
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>204. Please transmit to Zog I King of the Albanians the following
                            message: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Your cable of January 6<note n="62" xml:id="d29fn62">Sent direct
                                        to the President.</note> has been received with appreciation
                                    and I reciprocate your hope for the triumph of human rights and
                                    international justice. Franklin D. Roosevelt.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>You may add verbally that as yet no procedure has been established for
                            adherence to the principles of the Declaration by United Nations for
                            other than governments but that note has been taken of his request.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>